Path diagram for best fitting bivariate structural equation model (Cholesky model). The best fitting model was model composited of additive genetic factor (A), unique environment factor (E). The path of genetic factors between two visits is a21. The path of unique environmental factors between the phenotypes of the two visits is e21. The pathway a21 and a22 cannot be set to 0 while pathway e21 can be set to 0. rPH is the phenotypic correlation for PWV between visit 1 and visit 2. rg is the genetic correlation for PWV between visit 1 and visit 2. rg = COVA(1st visit, 2nd visit)/√ (VA 1st visit * VA 2nd visit), with COVA represents covariance and VA represents variance.

